00:00:00.950 --> 00:00:09.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : A requirement as part of our AOC certification is a demonstration or inspection flight to Kumasi and back.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:19.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : We would be having about eight Civil Aviation officials on and then also we will be having as passengers...

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:29.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : ...personnel of Africa World Airlines and SAS Group. So in all we have a total of twenty nine passengers on the flight to Kumasi and back.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:41.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : The flight time to.... I've checked from engineering and we don't have any defects on the aircraft...

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:47.000
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Which aircraft are we using?
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : We're using Nine-Golf-Alpha-Echo-Tango
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : We're using Tango ah...
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : We're using the Tango yeah... Nine-Golf-Alpha-Echo-Tango.

00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:53.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : From Accra, our flight number is Alpha Foxtrot Whiskey Nine Zero Six and we will be flying direct to Kumasi.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:04.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : The latest METAR that we have for Kumasi as at Oh Nine and Oh Eight hundred says the visibility is more than ten kilometers... yes, more than ten kilometers.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:11.500
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : We don't have any forecast data but over the last three METARs the trend is quite stable and the weather seems to be ok.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:21.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : And uh.. we don't have any NOTAMs that are affecting our, our flights....

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:33.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : For diversion, we are using Accra as our alternate in case of any problem.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:41.500
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Ok, and what are we using for diversion when coming back to Accra?

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:50.500
(Rustling of papers)
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : Coming back to Accra, we are using Benin. Yes, Cotonou which is Delta Bravo Bravo Bravo as our alternate.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:56.500
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Ok, and we know they have the correct fire category at Delta Bravo Bravo Bravo, ok.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:04.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : For fuel, three point three tons are already in tanks. You need to tell him the actual amount of fuel you require to relay out there before you move.

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:12.500
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Ok perfect, and we have to get the load sheet also.
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : Yeah, and basically that should be all on our side.

