EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : The good news is that we now have our latest Jeppessen manuals.
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Oh ok.
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : In fact, we have sent the copies there but one copy is here for dispatch.
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Right, I understand that.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.500
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Ok. The operating crew today is going to be... myself and...?

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:40.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : Gloria.. Sydney...
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : ...Bruce... and myself Tommy. Ok.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:49.500
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : We also have our Director of Flight Operations on board and some other dignitaries as well. Olivia is the standby crew.

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:58.500
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Ok. And I understand correct that the task for the flight today is to satisfy the GCAA that we can operate in a safe manner later on.
EMMANUEL LAMPTEY : Precisely.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:07.500
CAPT. TOMMY FJELD : Alright, so lets hope we can do that. I understand that the aircraft, there are no technical remarks at all and it's all been taken care of.

